<content start="624" end="625">
<component><class>org.concord.modeler.PageTextBox</class>
<width>500.0</width>
<height>300.0</height>
<title>&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body face=&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;
    &lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Click a button on the tool bar of the container on the left 
    will put the container&apos;s molecular editor into the state of action the 
    button specifies. &lt;/font&gt;

    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;To insert a particle, click for example one of the 
        insertion buttons (&amp;quot;&lt;img src=&quot;AddAtomC.gif&quot;&gt; &amp;quot;), you will be in 
        the mode of adding blue particles. Try clicking in the window of the 
        container. You should see a new particle is inserted to the location 
        you click. If you continue to click without switching action mode, you 
        will be able to insert as many blue particles as you want.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;
      &lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;To remove a particle, right-click (Windows) or 
        CTRL+click (Mac OS X) on it, and select &amp;quot;Cut&amp;quot; from the popup menu. 
        There are also a set of actions you can perform on the selected 
        particle from the popup menu.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;
      &lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;If you need to delete many particles at the same time, 
        for example, clear the container, please select the scissor button (&amp;quot;&lt;img src=&quot;BlockRemove.gif&quot;&gt; 
        &amp;quot;), and then hold down your mouse button and drag a rectangle. 
        Anything falling with the rectangular area will be remove all at once.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
      &lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;To heat the whole system up, select the 
        &amp;quot;Option&amp;gt;Toolbox&amp;gt;Quick Heat and Cool&amp;quot;. (Note: from the Option menu of 
        the model container, not the main Option menu above the page window). 
        You will see a bar with three buttons appearing on the right of the 
        container window. When this bar appears, click the button with an &amp;quot;up&amp;quot; 
        arrow to heat the system, and that with a &amp;quot;down&amp;quot; arrow to cool the 
        system. Warning: Do not heat too much, or you will drive the system 
        crazy.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;
      &lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;To heat or cool only some particles, use the Heat (&amp;quot;&lt;img src=&quot;HeatHere.gif&quot;&gt; 
        &amp;quot;) or Cool (&amp;quot;&lt;img src=&quot;CoolHere.gif&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;) Button, and then 
        click. The particles under the cover of the circles will be heated or 
        cooled. You will need to turn on the Kinetic Energy Shading mode (use 
        the check box right below the model container on the left) in order to 
        see the energy changes immediately.&lt;/font&gt;
      &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</title>
<opaque>false</opaque>
</component></content>

